This paper discusses the problem of navigating the tradeoff between privacy and utility in online social networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a model for utility that is associated with specific attributes of a user, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a heuristic greedy algorithm to solve the problem, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practical constraints on acceptable loss in utility per unit gain in privacy, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
